Package com.davidjarski.vfatreader

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Bytes
    Bytes defines static methods for converting contiguous bytes into larger data types.
    C
    C defines static final constants.
    Directory
    A Directory is a iterable list of DirectoryEntries.

    A factory method is provided to get the root directory of a Disk.
    The root directory is currently the only directory supported by this class.
    DirectoryEntry
    A DirectoryEntry is a data structure representing a single directory entry.
    Disk
    A Disk contains a reference to a FAT12 disk image and provides methods for reading the image.
    FAT
    A FAT is a data structure representing the file allocation table.
    Fat12Reader
    A Fat12Reader holds a reference to a Disk and provides methods for outputting the contents of the disk as required by Programming Assignment 3.
    Main
    Main is the entry point for the Programming Assignment 3 project.
    MBR
    An MBR is a data structure representing the master boot record.
    PrettyPrint
    PrettyPrint defines static methods for getting a formatted String and/or appending a formatted String to a StringBuilder.
